,Recommended,214170,4260970,"Posted: 5 July, 2012",all,Xelios,"Divine Divinity is a fantastic old-school RPG.  There's a little bit of everything here in one aspect or another: Ultima VII, Sacred, and the great Infinity Engine games with some Diablo hack-n-slash action thrown in--though most things not done quite as well.  The graphics (again, like the Infinity Engine games) have held up amazingly well and the game is still beautiful, boasting a soundtrack just as much so.There's a vast, incredibly detailed above-ground and subterranian world packed full of secrets, quests and treasure for you to discover.  The skill system is filled with useful abilities, very little filler and doesn't restrict you to your class skills; even if you start as a mage you can pick up some thief skills along the way if you desire, and chances are you'll want to.  Combat is satisfying and the difficulty seems just right.Not much point in playing as multiple characters due to the open skill system, but the game already packs dozens of hours.  Same price as GOG, so don't hesitate to buy it if you don't have hangups about playing older games."
