 RPG gameplay  could get a bit bored at the first couple of hours.Resolution possibley has to be set manually at the ini files fos some PC configurations. I found out that I dindt like the small characters at 1920x1080, so I am happily playing with the resolution set at 1600x900.Initial 'view distance' is bery short. It was OK on the old screen resolutions, but now at high resolution settings I definetly prefer my character to be able to see the enemies that are halph screen away. Fortunatelly, the view distance is actually a stat of the character that can be boosted with xp, so I used a mod from the begining of the game, adding to an item I am carrying the ""+12 view"" bonus.The open-world strucure can lead to some broken quests, so better to check comunity guides on the matter."
76561198045382534,Recommended,214170,27746879,"Posted: 26 November, 2016",all,Attiker,"About demons, heroes and cats.Divine Divinity is most likely one of the greatest isometric Hack-&Slay-RPGs of all time, including a well written story about demons, necromancers, heroes and cats. The land Rivellon is torn apart by war, civil unrest and greed...a group of fanatic villains and madmen created ways to bind a divinity for the sole reason of destroying the world. The tortured divinity managed to escape and blessed the upcoming hero with her divine light.What will happen next is for the player to decide. Rivellon is a very large land that contains many side stories, quests and characters. The player is able to choose out of six different heroes - warrior, mage and thief, every class has a female and male counterpart - and can further customize the hero with several skills, lots of weapons and many clothes. The graphics did age well and the combat is simple but enjoyable.I recommend Divine Divinity to everyone who likes Baldur's Gate, well written oldschool-RPGs and cats."
