76561198031328124,Recommended,214170,33559808,Posted: 15 July,all,Rizilliant,"If you like your games straight old school, with ZERO help, no tutorial, and everything on you, then this is right up your alley.. Any 'Help' that you need, YOU must locate inside books, listen carefully to conversations, or locate with your own eyes.. Holding 'Alt' reveals some items that youre able to loot, but things like levers, torches, and other interatable environment details must be located yourself.. They highlight when moused over, but thats it..I can see from very extremely limited time with this game, that its going to be very deep, rewarding, and difficult..You start by selectiong 1 of 3 classes Rogue, Warrior, Mage(2 of each class, of each gender, totalling 6).. Thats where the class system ends, and you can choose skills and stats however you like.. More akin to a classless system..Combat is real time, ith a pause feature.. You can hotkey abilities, potions etc. but can only have one of them equipped at a time, and is used with the right mouse button.. Tap a hotkey to swap it, and then right click to use it.. Your normal attack is left clik.. You can use either Stamina abilities, or Mana abilities via this method..Its actually visually appealing, even though its 15yrs old.. I will say, Dont bother trying it on your native resolution, as above its original res, the texts, and EVERYTHING becomes so tiny, its difficult to read, see, and even click on items/enemies.. I dropped it down to 1260x800, and obviously everything was MUCH easier to see, AND there was ZERO loss in graphical fidelity.. Still looked great!In all honesty, this IS my type of game... Im not sure if its because I have such a large unplayed backlog, if Im just not feeling this game, or if I just not in the mood because I know its going to take a serious investment learning, and playing throghj such a deep game.. But I am indeed having a hard time gett6ing started.. It doesnt help that theres no sense of direction, or help at the start.. Very much ""heres your character.. GO!""  But its definitely going to be epic, if I can get myself over the initial hump!If youre looking for a more casual game, remeniscent of todays handheld, dumbed down crap, look elsewhere!"
