,Not Recommended,214170,13723314,"Posted: 30 December, 2014",all,Reptilian,"First off I have to mention that this game is incredibly buggy or at least the Steam version is, since it's apparently lacking a major patch. There are a ton of quests that don't work at all or are partially broken. Some people even said that they can't finish the game because of some major bugs. Also, avoid exploring an area before you have a quest that requires you to go there, MANY quests can be broken by doing stuff before you're asked to.I've played this game many years before but I returned to it now after about 10 years.Combat: You click on enemies once and you also have to spam potions. Spamming potions is mandatory since the developers found it very fun and innovative to not give you health OR mana regen. This doesn't add anything to the game, it only makes it tedious. You only have to spend a few hundred gold coins on mana potions and then you can spam spam spam. Basically, thanks to the game trying to be ""tactical"" and♥♥♥♥♥♥by forcing you to use potions, you have infinite health and mana.As you can imagine the mage class is probably very fun to play.Actually it ain't. There are 2-3 spells that are worth your time and they look like crap. Also, you're going to have to rely on melee/ranged a lot since you don't want to waste mana on the easy mobs.The starting spell of the mage called ""meteor strike"" is a yellow football followed by an ugly looking smoke effect. That's what you're gonna have to use for the first 20-30 levels because most of the other spells are pathetic. The spells aren't satisfying to use AT ALL, it's depressing. The effects are boring to look at, they lack power, and the sound effects don't make you feel like you're actually a powerful mage. You can also cheese the game with Freeze and frost weapons.The quests are actually the best part of the game, they're rarely fetch quests or ""kill 10 sewer rats"" quests but even after you've done them all you feel like you had little impact on the world besides getting special responses from unnamed NPCs based on your reputation level. The reputation system, however, is broken, some quests give you +0 rep and some substract reputation when they shouldn't (you saved that ♥♥♥♥♥ from the zombie? -4 rep for you). Again, more and more bugs.The music is great as well, it makes the game atmospheric, too bad the game itself is lacking in substance.The storyline is simple and boring, you have to kill a cult that wants to destroy the world. The dialogue is so bad it's as if it was written by a 12 year old, they try too hard to make it sound funny and most of the time it's not. The animations are bugged when you play it on a modern system, most animations are running at very high speed and look odd.Only play this game if you just want to waste time playing an isometric RPG just for the sake of doing it. It's literally a big pile of♥♥♥♥♥♥ it even has the bugs. It's not even a good Diablo clone, there are better clones out there, like the Sacred series, Titan Quest, Torchlight, Path of Exile, etc. Some people compared this game to the Ultima series so try out those games instead of  torturing yourself with this crap."
