76561197994073217,Recommended,214170,14399912,"Posted: 9 February, 2015",all,egvoidl,"I played this game numerous times when it came out. I loved it then, and I love it now. This time I have discovered a bug/exploit that might be helpful to survivor players. The bug involves the hide in shadows skill. When in a dungeon or at night outside, you can target an enemy and then activate your hide in shadows, the glitch is you become totally invisible, and can maintain attack in this state for as long as you like. It doesn't drain stamina. The catch is to deactivate it you have to find a light source. This is usually pretty easy to accomplish by the numerous torches and piles of gold littering a dungeon. If you don't want to look around, carry a ruby or other gem and just drop it, it will provide enough light to cancel the shadows."
