,Recommended,214170,8044927,"Posted: 14 December, 2013",all,"AJ, Lord of Chaos","-Classic gem of a RPG, often over-looked-It's an action-RPG with a huge open overworld, countless dungeons and quests. Pretty hard because you easily run into dangerous enemies while exploring the map. Even standard enemies give you a beating and some bosses are almost unfair. Like in Diablo loot is randomized and plenty, monsters come in packs. It also shares the same music style. The PC can mix his skills from all the talent trees but specializing is recommended. Beside the fighting there is a lot of talking, doing interesting quests with twists and riddles so there is stuff beside pure combat."
,Recommended,214170,8046192,"Posted: 14 December, 2013",all,ArseBiscuits,"One of my favourite RPGs of all time, it has beautiful isometric artwork, fun combat and an intriguing plot with good characters.The artwork is great in my opinion, coming at the end of an era of great iosmetric games and utilising the available technology post-millenium, making me sad that this genre was all but dropped for a decade.Combat is a kind of Diablo-like with left clicking to melee and right clicking to fling spells and a button to lock on to enemies if you need the extra accuracy. I found it a lot of fun, although some abilities are quite unbalanced. There is certainly plenty of scope for roleplaying and building custom classes (there are starting classes but no restrictions on gear or abilities) but you might find yourself using some abilities and skills simply because they're very effective.The plot is interesting, with plenty of intrigue and wonder and it takes you to many interesting places, varied environments and great characters abound. It also has a good sense of humour, without overdoing it, something that Larian are usually quite good at.In summary, this game feels like Diablo got a shot of Baldur's Gate and a taste of Elder Scrolls and I feel it is highly underrated. If you enjoy RPGs you shouldn't miss out on this gem."
