,Recommended,214170,8825876,"Posted: 23 January, 2014",all,M. Doucet,"This one is a tough one. Like the other games in this series, you get out of it what you're willing to put into it. For those essentially willing to relearn an RPG from scratch and grapple with a game that didn't age well, you absolutely would not be disappointed. As always, Larian excels in their storytelling and spins a deep and compelling tale once you start to figure out what's going on and how to play the game. Modern RPG fans should likely pass this one up as it eschews convention at every turn and is notoriously difficult to play, yet alone play well. Old schoolers who are willing to make the investment in this title will be well-rewarded by its depth, complexity, and amazing ending. 8/10."
,Recommended,214170,25000499,"Posted: 18 August, 2016",all,SDDubya,"This game is tons of fun.  It's made by the same people who made Divinity: Original Sin, and the same sense of humor is in this game.  The gameplay is like a cross between Baldur's Gate and Diablo II.  There's real time combat with pause, and the skill trees are really a lot of fun.  My first playthrough, I went as a summoner, and was able to summon 10 skeletons and a strong knight, and a bunch of rats as well.  But you can also play as pure melee, or as a ranger, or any hybrid class you can think of.  My advice: invest in the skill that lets you place runes in your equipment.  You can easily double your base stats this way.  Also, don't invest points in magic, as you can buy magic skill books, and you will have a ton of money as you progress.If you like ARPGs, quests that can be long and hard to figure out sometimes, a bunch of freedom, and a huge open world to explore and develop your character in any way you can imagine, then this game is for you.  It's one of my all-time favorites."
,Recommended,214170,25867776,"Posted: 5 October, 2016",all,Deckard[HZ],"Decent diablo-style rpg, good if you're looking for that kind of gameplay. It's also very open ended and the enemies are not scaled to your level, for better or worse.Word of Warning for new players: Weapons and Armor have COMPLETELY RANDOM stats. Even the unique set armor and weapons. The stats are decided when you kill a tough enemy or find the item. I'm not talking diablo-style random where it can have a random value added to str or whatnot, I'm talking totally friggin random. You can find a dragon-armor setpiece (best in the game, at least potentially) with literally anywhere from 2-12 mods, all of which vary incredibly. If you want to get the best gear in this game, you will have to save and reload until you find the best roll. Not that I have anything against random rolls, but the game doesn't tell you about this and it is soooo ridiculously random you could reload 50-100 times and never get the same stats twice (and I would know >.>)."
