,Recommended,214170,26949731,"Posted: 23 November, 2016",all,Raynaldo,"An incredibly enthralling and rewarding experience. Very long to play through, but never feels repetitive or grindy (monsters don't respawn). Works great in Ultrawide HD (2560x1080), which is no small feat for a game this old.There is a few things you should know before you start playing the game.1. BUCK daggers. There is very low variety of dagger weapons, so if you want to rely on assassin's kiss you will be under-powered most of the time. Besides, you can't dual wield, and pairing a shield as high as your shoulder with a dinky dagger makes you look like a retard.2. Craft magic potions to heal yourself. Using the Restoration skill is a lot more resource efficient and handy in combat than chugging healing potions. You will find enough of the latter to use in emergency when your health is too low.3. Skills in the game can be raised three ways- points from leveling up, items (in the form of a skill book) and quest rewards. There are several quests that reward you Restoration, and a book of it you can find at an easy place, so don't waste points maxing it out (max level is 5).4. If you want to reach ALL the loot, you will find the Telekinesis skill useful (I could only retrieve the aforementioned Restoration book with a level 2 Telekinesis skill).5. Scorpion traps are absolutely OP.  Just throw a couple of them at any boss (by using the trap skill) and they will most likely kill it for you.6. Gold will be plentiful. Ignore the Trading skill.7. Save the game often, in different slots.8. Regeneration is useless. Don't bother. It's too slow to be worth the points and you'll get plenty of potions anyway."
